[SN]TITLE[SN]
Cheltenham Town 4-1 Boreham Wood

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
National League leaders Cheltenham Town stepped up their automatic promotion push with victory over Boreham Wood.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
After the late arrival of Boreham Wood's team bus delayed kick-off by 15 minutes, Danny Wright scored from the spot after Danny Woodards' foul on Dan Holman, who then put the Robins 2-0 up.
Harry Pell was felled by Scott Doe and Wright added a second penalty before Danny Haynes replied from 25 yards.
But Holman's strike in stoppage time sealed a fine win for Cheltenham.
Gary Johnson's side are three points clear at the top, while Boreham Wood sit inside the relegation zone in 21st position, one point away from safety.
Cheltenham Town boss Gary Johnson told BBC Radio Gloucestershire:
