"It was an enjoyable afternoon, we had to work hard and I thought our spirit was very good; it's very difficult to play the beautiful game on a bumpy pitch.
"I know we've been on bumpy pitches, so a lot of your passes are headers - I know that sounds stupid - but we had to be good passers of a ball with our head.
"The boys showed good control and four goals is a very good return."
